{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "25", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "09", "S": "32"}}, "news": [{"title": "Puravankara acquires 14.57-acre land parcel in Mandur, Bengaluru", "para": "Puravankara has acquired a 14.57-acre land parcel in Bengaluru's Mandur, Budigere, with a potential gross development value of \u20b92,300 crore. This acquisition, comprising both purchased land and a joint development agreement, will yield approximately 1.8 million sq ft of saleable area. The company's Bengaluru developable landbank now stands at 25.61 million sq ft.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/puravankara-acquires-1457-acres-in-bengaluru-a-boon-for-real-estate-development/131304740?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-235538/131304740.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "No decision to dismantle LIFE Mission housing scheme: Kerala's LSG minister", "para": "Kerala's Local Self Government Minister K M Shaji has clarified that the UDF government has no plans to disband the LIFE Mission housing scheme. He stated that restoring powers to grama sabhas does not equate to scrapping the project, emphasizing that the new government aims to correct shortcomings rather than dismantle existing initiatives.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/local-self-government-minister-clarifies-no-plans-to-dismantle-life-mission-housing-project/131301044?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-13822/131301044.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Bihar government seeks \u20b91,600 crore from centre for rural housing", "para": "In a significant move to bolster rural development, Bihar has formally requested the Centre to disburse Rs 1,600 crore under the 'Mother Sanction' for the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana\u2013Gramin. With the state's Single Nodal Account running low, timely support for beneficiaries is at risk.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/bihar-government-requests-1600-crore-funds-for-rural-housing-initiative/131300972?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-273840/131300972.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}